{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"As the demand for content for iPad increases, so does the need for tools to create that content. Mac OS X offers well-integrated automation technologies and tools, including Automator, Services, and AppleScript, that are ideal for generating content. Geared towards professional and non-professionals alike, this session will include hands-on tutorials covering how to use the automation technologies of Mac OS X to create and distribute HTML-based content for iPad."}],"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2010\/302\/","overridingTitle":"Read Transcript","type":"reference"},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"sections":[],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"role":"sampleCode","title":"Automating the Creation of iPad Content","roleHeading":"WWDC10"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC10"]]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc10-302-automating-the-creation-of-ipad-content"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC10-302-Automating-the-Creation-of-iPad-Content","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by reading the transcript and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"reference","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"article","references":{"WWDC10-Icon.png":{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC10-Icon.png","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC10-Icon.png